Three men were on Monday brought before an Igbosere Magistratesâ€™ Court in Lagos for allegedly vandalising a Toyota Prado and stealing its spare parts worth N1.9 million. The accused, Geofrey Iroegbu (58), Amos Amos (27) and Saliu Suleman (35), whose residential addresses were not given, are facing a two-count charge of conspiracy and stealing. The trio, however, pleaded not guilty to the charges. Earlier, the Prosecutor, Insp. Okete Ejime, told the court that the accused vandalized one Prado Jeep, marked FKJ 426 DV, belonging to the complainant, Mrs Ayodele Akindele. He said that the defendants vandalized one Prado Jeep marked FKJ 426 DV, belonging to the complainant, Mrs Ayodele Akindele. According to the prosecutor, the stolen vehicle parts included brain box, display and opening units and the windshield of the vehicle, all valued N1.9 million. He said the offences contravened Sections 287 (7) and 411 of the Criminal Law of Lagos State, 2019. Counsel to the accused, Mr Emmanuel Okedi, urged the court to grant bail to the defendants on liberal terms. The Magistrate, Mrs H. O. Omisore, granted them N100, 000 bail each with two sureties each in like sum. She adjourned the case until Feb. 25 for mention. (NAN)